Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a new paradigm of self-organized control for robots, specifically focusing on a muscle-tendon driven arm-shoulder system. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for the controller, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for the controller, which could also fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
